</div><div id="nb89">
<p><span class="spip_note_ref">[<a href="#nh89" class="spip_note" title="Footnotes 89" rev="footnote">89</a>]&nbsp;</span>This last issue of <i>Révision</i> was entitled ‘‘Courrier des Camps’</i> (‘Camps Newsletter’) and was produced half in French, half in Spanish. It was directed at, and circulated round, the Spanish revolutionaries in the concentration camps created by French ‘democracy’ for the Spanish Republicans fleeing Franco. On the camps, see René Grando, Jacques Queralt &amp; Xavier Febrès, <i>Vous avez la mémoire courte... </i>(Marcevol: Editions du Chiendent, 1981); Denis Peschanski, ‘Les camps d’internement français’ in<i> L’Histoire</i> no.129 (1990), 104-9; Louis Stein, <i>Beyond Death and Exile. The Spanish Republicans in France, 1939-1955 </i>(Cambridge, Massachussets: Harvard University Press, 1979).</p>
